text: Septa may refer to: ==Biology== * Septa (gastropod), a gastropod genus in the family Ranellidae * Septa, the plural of septum, in anatomy, a wall of tissue dividing a cavity (e.g., in the nose) * Septa, plural for septum (coral), the stony ridges forming part of the corallites of corals ==Other uses== * SEPTA, the Southeastern Pennsylvania Transportation Authority *Septa Unella, a fictional character in A Song of Ice and Fire and its TV adaptation, Game Of Thrones
title: Septa
